    "what_description": "Psychotria yorubensis is a species of flowering plant in the family Rubiaceae. It is a shrub with simple, opposite, elliptical to ovate leaves that are 2-8 cm long and 1-5 cm wide, with a petiole 2-10 mm long. The leaves are glabrous, with a chartaceous texture and a cuneate base. The plant produces small, greenish-white flowers in axillary cymes, with 4-5-merous calyx and corolla. The species is endemic to Nigeria, where it grows in the tropical rainforest at elevations up to 1,000 m.",
