    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Psychotria yorubensis are anti-inflammatory and antioxidant, with potential for treating various diseases. The anti-inflammatory properties of this plant are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and saponins, which can help reduce inflammation and alleviate pain associated with conditions such as arthritis. The antioxidant properties of Psychotria yorubensis are linked to the bioactive compounds like phenolic acids, which can protect against oxidative stress and cell damage, thus preventing diseases like cancer and neurodegenerative disorders. Additionally, the plant's antimicrobial properties can be utilized to combat infections caused by bacteria and fungi, making it a potential alternative to antibiotics. The immunomodulatory properties of Psychotria yorubensis are also noteworthy, suggesting its potential in modulating the immune system and treating conditions like autoimmune diseases.",
