    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Psychotria yorubensis are utilized due to its medicinal properties. Tea and infusion are prepared by steeping the leaves in hot water, often used to treat fever and respiratory issues. Tincture is made by soaking the leaves in a solvent, typically ethanol, to create a concentrated extract for systemic use. Decoction involves boiling the leaves in water to release their active compounds, commonly used to treat gastrointestinal problems. A salve is prepared by mixing the leaves with a carrier oil, typically coconut or olive oil, to create a topical application for skin irritations and wounds.",
